Tool: coloc (https://github.com/cran/coloc)

1) Input file format

pvalues
P-values for each SNP in dataset

N
Number of samples in dataset

MAF
minor allele frequency of the variants

beta
regression coefficient for each SNP from dataset

varbeta
variance of beta

type
the type of data in dataset 1 - either "quant" or "cc" to denote quantitative or case-control

s
for a case control dataset, the proportion of samples in dataset 1 that are cases

snp
SNP rsid.

2) run coloc

R --slave --vanilla --args Input1.txt Input2.txt < COLOC.R

